sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.country_name
FROM countries c
JOIN data_points dp ON c.country_id = dp.country_id;

SELECT SUM(population) AS total_population
FROM countries
WHERE region = 'Europe' AND population BETWEEN 1000000 AND 10000000;

external_knowledge:
- The 'beacons of measurement' metaphorically represent the indicators;
- 'Shine brighter than the common light' signifies that the average values are higher than a standard threshold;
- 'Illuminating the European continent' refers to the focus on countries in the Europe region;
- 'Threshold of 100' corresponds to the condition that the average value must be greater than 100.
